{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place bread in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>30 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place onions and garlic in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter, and divide pollock fillets between Varoma dish and tray. Place covered Varoma into position then cook <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma then scrape base of mixing bowl with spatula to minimise burning.","Add to mixing bowl steamed cod, cream, 100 g flour and pepper then cook <nobr>7 min\/100°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and stir in salt and reserved chopped parsley. Leave to cool then refrigerate for approx. 30 minutes. Meanwhile, place remaining 100 g flour in a bowl and beaten eggs in another bowl. Heat oil in a deep fat fryer or heavy based saucepan to 170°C.","With oiled hands, take 2 Tbsp mixture and place an olive inside. Roll into a croquette then dip in flour, beaten eggs and then reserved breadcrumbs. Repeat with remaining mixture and olives.","Deep fry for approx. 3 minutes then transfer to paper towel to absorb excess oil. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["20 g fresh parsley, leaves only","150 g stale white bread, torn in pieces","250 g onions, quartered","2 garlic cloves","100 g salted butter, diced","600 g pollock fillets, skinless, boneless","200 g double cream","200 g plain flour","1 pinch ground black pepper","2 tsp fine sea salt","3 large eggs, beaten","sunflower oil, plus extra for greasing hands","40 g pitted black olives"]}],"id":"r144433","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-7l6l1fEfzNc\/XZaoMsL6tkI\/AAAAAAAAhH0\/4YO8I-59o_wbuUm8GU_lpcj-1oAEMiWqgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_grcWzNgKhq5Jt4gd.png","title":"Pollock Croquettes with Olives","publishedAt":"2017-03-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.7 g","fa